value.0: My name is Daelan - once of the Uthgardt Red Tiger Tribe. I have traveled much of the civilized lands since the day I have left my people.
I am not one to boast of my own abilities, yet the skill and ferocity of the Uthgardt tribes are well known throughout the North.
I doubt you will find any other axeman for hire who is my equal. I ask only for a share of the gold and treasures we find.
As you wish. If you need me you can always find me here... unless I join up with someone who has need of my skills, that is.
You already have someone with you, my <lord/lady>. Traveling in such a large group is not my style.
As you wish. If you are alone, then perhaps we can make a good team.
<StartCheck>[Failure]</Start> No, I think it is best if we don't join up. If you are by yourself, though, I believe we can make a great team.
<StartCheck>[Success]</Start> Perhaps I was overthinking things. Very well, my <lord/lady>. My skills are yours to command.
You will not regret this, my <lord/lady>. My skills are yours to command.
You have returned. Is there something I can help you with?
Yes, <sir/madam>. Is there something you need?
As you wish.
If that is what you want. Do you really want to part ways?
As you wish.
Then we shall part ways, though I will wait at the Trade of Blades in case you reconsider and wish to join up again.
I'm sorry, but I have joined with somebody else.
As you wish.

value.0: Thank you, <FirstName>. But for now we should return to the task at hand. Neverwinter is counting on you.
Beware, lest you incur my wrath.
I'll be going now.
I could use a good warrior. Welcome aboard, Daelan.
Fine. Forget I asked.
<StartCheck>[Persuade]</Start> Come on, it's not such a large party. Please reconsider and join us.
Never mind.
I think I'll do better on my own.
No, I misspoke.
Yes, I am certain.
I'd like to buy off some of the loot that you picked up.
I'd like to buy off some of the loot that you picked up.
Never mind.
